## CRITICAL EMERGENCY PROTOCOL — Bus Factor 1

This project is maintained by a solo engineer. The `/.handoff` directory contains living documentation that enables any developer to take over immediately.

**RULE:** Every time you make a structural change, add a dependency, or complete a feature, you MUST autonomously update the relevant files in the `/.handoff` directory. Before formatting a `git push` command, you must update `/.handoff/03_ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` to reflect the exact state of the pushed code.

**Handoff files:**
- `/.handoff/01_SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md` — Update when: adding integrations, changing database schema, modifying environment variables, altering the tech stack.
- `/.handoff/02_OPERATIONS_AND_DEPLOYMENT.md` — Update when: changing build/deploy steps, adding scripts, modifying CI/CD, changing hosting config.
- `/.handoff/03_ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md` — Update EVERY push: current state, latest changes, known bugs, feature status.

A pre-push git hook enforces this. If you forget, the push will be blocked.
